external_concepts.name: Action
external_concepts.label: Action
external_concepts.definition: An action performed by a direct agent and indirect participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies the exact expectation of each argument/role.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/04/16/announcing-schema-org-actions/) and [Actions overview document](https://schema.org/docs/actions.html).

external_concepts.name: Service Channel
external_concepts.label: ServiceChannel
external_concepts.definition: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

external_concepts.name: Message
external_concepts.label: Message
external_concepts.definition: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

external_concepts.name: Language
external_concepts.label: Language
external_concepts.definition: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the alternateName property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using ComputerLanguage.

external_concepts.name: Place
external_concepts.label: Place
external_concepts.definition: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

external_concepts.name: Question
external_concepts.label: Question
external_concepts.definition: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

external_concepts.name: Join Action
external_concepts.label: JoinAction
external_concepts.definition:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
* FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.
